header.gameNote: AMERICA EAST MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT WEST HARTFORD CT

article.headline: Vermont 76, UMBC 59
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Maurice Joseph scored 19 points and Marqus Blakely had 18 points and 12 rebounds to lead Vermont to an easy 76-59 victory over Maryland-Baltimore County on Saturday night in the first round of the America East Conference tournament. The win moved the Catamounts (23-9) into Sunday night's semifinal against New Hampshire. Joseph was 4-for-6 from 3-point range and Blakely, the two-time conference Player of the Year who didn't win the award this season, notched his 16th double-double of the season. It was the 43rd of his career. Blakely also chipped in five assists and three blocks. The win was Vermont's third of the season against the Retrievers (4-26). Evan Fjeld added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the second-seeded Catamounts. Shawn Grant had 17 points and Adrian Satchell 14 for seventh-seeded UMBC.
